1010
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:19,000
Went to the same war as a matter of fact.

1011
01:03:19,000 --> 01:03:21,000
You?

1012
01:03:21,000 --> 01:03:22,000
Back here again?

1013
01:03:22,000 --> 01:03:24,000
Yes, I'm back here again.

1014
01:03:24,000 --> 01:03:27,000
In this time, I'm not going to rush home.

1015
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:28,000
They understood.

1016
01:03:28,000 --> 01:03:31,000
I got very good treatment and care.

1017
01:03:31,000 --> 01:03:39,000
During that period, the army regrouped, recovered, prepared to take care of business.

1018
01:03:39,000 --> 01:03:44,000
I was told to rebuild your strength by going out and learning how to ski.

1019
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:47,000
Send I known for its slopes and stuff like that.

1020
01:03:47,000 --> 01:03:49,000
And so, flying, I've gone and tried.

1021
01:03:49,000 --> 01:03:52,000
I never ski before you understand.

1022
01:03:52,000 --> 01:03:55,000
Went out to the training area where they teach skiing.

1023
01:03:55,000 --> 01:04:03,000
And they gave me skis, flagboard, two straps, one across the insta, one across the hill.

1024
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:06,000
No boots, nothing else.

1025
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:09,000
And I did like you might expect you ski by the way.

1026
01:04:09,000 --> 01:04:10,000
Yes.

1027
01:04:10,000 --> 01:04:12,000
So you understand what kind of trouble I had.

1028
01:04:12,000 --> 01:04:15,000
I did not do very well at all.

1029
01:04:15,000 --> 01:04:20,000
But I managed to get back off the hill and went back to the hospital area.

1030
01:04:21,000 --> 01:04:29,000
But that taught me a lesson about trying to ski with that kind of equipment.

1031
01:04:29,000 --> 01:04:35,000
I eventually come back to the unit now in March, back to the regiment.

1032
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:41,000
And the back in the base camp before I moved up to the regiment.

1033
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:46,000
They had a new executive officer in the regiment.

1034
01:04:46,000 --> 01:04:50,000
Lieutenant Colonel Arlento, Marsani.

1035
01:04:50,000 --> 01:04:53,000
And you'll see why I remember that name in a few minutes.

1036
01:04:53,000 --> 01:05:01,000
And when I get back to the regimental rear, and I meet the battalion exec,

1037
01:05:01,000 --> 01:05:05,000
he enroves me to this regimental exec.

1038
01:05:05,000 --> 01:05:11,000
And the battalion execs said, we're going to put back to the battalion and become,

1039
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:14,000
he'll put them into an S3 operation.

1040
01:05:14,000 --> 01:05:18,000
He's been in combat, he understands he can help us there.

1041
01:05:18,000 --> 01:05:20,000
Or a sign that would look at me.

1042
01:05:20,000 --> 01:05:22,000
Lieutenant, how you feel?

1043
01:05:22,000 --> 01:05:24,000
I feel pretty good, sir.

1044
01:05:24,000 --> 01:05:27,000
We're going to put them into a company.

1045
01:05:27,000 --> 01:05:28,000
Why?

1046
01:05:28,000 --> 01:05:31,000
Because the company picked from me was L company.

1047
01:05:31,000 --> 01:05:32,000
Sound familiar?

1048
01:05:32,000 --> 01:05:33,000
Company I was in, men and four.

1049
01:05:33,000 --> 01:05:36,000
They had lost all of the officers and a few of the insurgents.

1050
01:05:36,000 --> 01:05:39,000
They needed some leadership up there.

1051
01:05:39,000 --> 01:05:42,000
Battalion agent said, but sir, he just got...

1052
01:05:42,000 --> 01:05:44,000
He's going to go to the company.

1053
01:05:44,000 --> 01:05:46,000
Yes, sir.

1054
01:05:46,000 --> 01:05:51,000
So I ended up going back to K company, L company, excuse me.

1055
01:05:51,000 --> 01:05:53,000
And he's correct.

1056
01:05:53,000 --> 01:05:56,000
We had all the officers been gone.

1057
01:05:56,000 --> 01:05:58,000
We got lost.

1058
01:05:58,000 --> 01:06:02,000
Somebody in the open had a couple of key insurgents that knew me and I knew them.

1059
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:05,000
So I'm now in the company commander.

1060
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:09,000
And we organized what we had.

1061
01:06:09,000 --> 01:06:12,000
We had gotten some new lieutenants, second lieutenants.

1062
01:06:12,000 --> 01:06:16,000
Still all black or white replacements at this point.

1063
01:06:16,000 --> 01:06:18,000
By that time we were integrated.

1064
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:19,000
I failed to mention one point.

1065
01:06:19,000 --> 01:06:21,000
Let me go back a little bit.

1066
01:06:21,000 --> 01:06:28,000
Mac in August, before I got 201 when I got my first loan,

1067
01:06:28,000 --> 01:06:34,000
the regiment commander, Colonel C.C. Sloan,

1068
01:06:34,000 --> 01:06:39,000
had been told by the adjutant we got incoming replacements,

1069
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:43,000
called for up by M.O.F. military operations,

1070
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:47,000
military specialties, but not by race.

1071
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:49,000
And Sloan said, put them where they're needed.

1072
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:51,000
Put them where they're needed.

1073
01:06:51,000 --> 01:06:54,000
Dr. C. took care of the integration within the NIFE infantry.

1074
01:06:54,000 --> 01:06:57,000
Went to the battalions, spread them out.

1075
01:06:57,000 --> 01:07:03,000
And when I got my first integrated soldier, he was a...

1076
01:07:04,000 --> 01:07:09,000
American, Mexican American, from Texas.

1077
01:07:09,000 --> 01:07:12,000
And when he came in, I told my patuist,

1078
01:07:12,000 --> 01:07:15,000
I don't let anything happen to that guy.

1079
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:17,000
He's our first one non-blank.

1080
01:07:17,000 --> 01:07:19,000
We're not going to hurt him at all.

1081
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:23,000
And he said, yes sir, we'll take care of that.

1082
01:07:23,000 --> 01:07:25,000
And with that we became integrated.

1083
01:07:25,000 --> 01:07:29,000
And so now the division integrated.

1084
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:32,000
And by the time we were in the fighting,

1085
01:07:32,000 --> 01:07:35,000
we had black company commanders and white battalions,

1086
01:07:35,000 --> 01:07:36,000
and so forth.

1087
01:07:36,000 --> 01:07:38,000
So we're doing quite well.

1088
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:40,000
When I got back today...

1089
01:07:40,000 --> 01:07:43,000
It was military necessity that re-witching.

1090
01:07:43,000 --> 01:07:45,000
It was military necessity.

1091
01:07:45,000 --> 01:07:47,000
It was the need for bodies.

1092
01:07:47,000 --> 01:07:49,000
Yeah, there's so forth in the house.

1093
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:52,000
It was...it had nothing to do with the executive order.

1094
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:57,000
The fact that we were combat, where people qualified,

1095
01:07:57,000 --> 01:08:00,000
and the commanders recognized their soldiers,

1096
01:08:00,000 --> 01:08:05,000
put them where they needed military necessity.

1097
01:08:05,000 --> 01:08:08,000
And that's the way we operated.

1098
01:08:08,000 --> 01:08:11,000
By the time I got back to the regiment,

1099
01:08:11,000 --> 01:08:15,000
it would have been about...

1100
01:08:15,000 --> 01:08:20,000
I guess April, I can check my book for you to find out

1101
01:08:20,000 --> 01:08:22,000
what that time was.

1102
01:08:22,000 --> 01:08:28,000
And we were in a base area.

1103
01:08:28,000 --> 01:08:33,000
The division was still engaged.

1104
01:08:33,000 --> 01:08:36,000
I am now a company commander.

1105
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:40,000
Lieutenant, first lieutenant.

1106
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:44,000
And we got a white officer, Captain, assigned to us

1107
01:08:44,000 --> 01:08:47,000
to be the company commander.

1108
01:08:48,000 --> 01:08:53,000
And he had not been in combat before.

1109
01:08:53,000 --> 01:08:57,000
The company had completely integrated by this time.

1110
01:08:57,000 --> 01:09:01,000
Then we had low-and-discussive captain myself.

1111
01:09:01,000 --> 01:09:03,000
And he said, okay.

1112
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:06,000
I want you to keep doing what you've been doing to be in charge.

1113
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:10,000
I'll take care of the base area and support you.

1114
01:09:10,000 --> 01:09:14,000
And that's all I finished to war in Korea.

1115
01:09:14,000 --> 01:09:18,000
With that arrangement,

1116
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:28,000
I should point out that by that time I had received two purple hearts.

1117
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:35,000
Receive a silver star for the operations back in the breaking out

1118
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:37,000
of the Poosing perimeter.

1119
01:09:37,000 --> 01:09:41,000
I took a Hill 201, I got my first one.

1120
01:09:41,000 --> 01:09:47,000
And it's now into May.

1121
01:09:47,000 --> 01:09:51,000
Things are going, we're moving gradually ahead.

1122
01:09:51,000 --> 01:09:55,000
But by that time they started rotating people home.

1123
01:09:55,000 --> 01:09:59,000
And I was able to rotate home.

1124
01:09:59,000 --> 01:10:02,000
Leaving the regiment.

1125
01:10:02,000 --> 01:10:08,000
Came back to the states.

1126
01:10:08,000 --> 01:10:17,000
Went off to, I was assigned to camp Edwards and Massachusetts.

1127
01:10:17,000 --> 01:10:21,000
Army is completely integrated now, up to a point.

1128
01:10:21,000 --> 01:10:26,000
Up at camp Edwards, they're one black company.

1129
01:10:26,000 --> 01:10:33,000
And their job was post police and kitchen work, kitchen,

1130
01:10:33,000 --> 01:10:37,000
cooking for the soldiers, small base.

1131
01:10:37,000 --> 01:10:44,000
And our job was to police to post police picking up trash and cooking

1132
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:49,000
soldiers for the white soldiers in the white unit.

1133
01:10:49,000 --> 01:10:53,000
That unit was all black I might add.

1134
01:10:53,000 --> 01:10:58,000
And I did not cut to that very much, but I've been in combat.

1135
01:10:58,000 --> 01:11:02,000
I've done a pretty good job, I thought, now I'm back in this kind of situation.

1136
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:05,000
And so I started complaining.

1137
01:11:05,000 --> 01:11:09,000
I called my brand, my telephone and say, look, I know what you got got me out here.

1138
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:13,000
I'm still on competitive tour, I understand that too.

1139
01:11:13,000 --> 01:11:18,000
And what, don't you think I deserve something better than this?

1140
01:11:18,000 --> 01:11:20,000
Within an hour, so I got to call back.

1141
01:11:20,000 --> 01:11:25,000
You're being transferred to any town get, any town get military reservations,

1142
01:11:25,000 --> 01:11:28,000
which is a basic training for soldiers.

1143
01:11:28,000 --> 01:11:39,000
And I went from camp Edwards to any town gap as a company commander, basic training.

1144
01:11:39,000 --> 01:11:42,000
It was there that I've been more to captain.

1145
01:11:42,000 --> 01:11:46,000
It was there that I got integrated into the regular army.

1146
01:11:46,000 --> 01:11:50,000
Orders come in and I'm in tall cotton, happy about that.

1147
01:11:50,000 --> 01:11:56,000
Training my unit, we're doing a great job turning out basic trainees.

1148
01:11:56,000 --> 01:12:08,000
Also, after industry training soldiers, I was also selected to go to signal of some communication course infantry.

1149
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:13,000
Learn how to become a commo communication officer in an infantry unit.

1150
01:12:13,000 --> 01:12:15,000
Why was I selected for that?

1151
01:12:15,000 --> 01:12:18,000
Because I had been a signal officer and I said, okay, he can do that.

1152
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:25,000
Big difference between pole climbing and stringing wire and being a guy in charge of communication on the ground.

1153
01:12:25,000 --> 01:12:29,000
But I went off to school.

1154
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:40,000
I come back to any town gap after the period of school training, which would about maybe nine weeks.

1155
01:12:40,000 --> 01:12:45,000
And was then my family stayed by the way when I was in any town gap.

1156
01:12:45,000 --> 01:12:48,000
They stayed in Philadelphia.

1157
01:12:48,000 --> 01:12:55,000
And I would go back and forth.

1158
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:59,000
Got orders to Germany.

1159
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:02,000
So just, okay.

1160
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:03,000
We can do that.

1161
01:13:03,000 --> 01:13:04,000
Pack up the bags.

1162
01:13:04,000 --> 01:13:17,000
We now have two daughters.

1163
01:13:17,000 --> 01:13:22,000
I'm not sure did I mention the fact that when my first daughter was born, I'm going back with active duty.

1164
01:13:22,000 --> 01:13:29,000
If I didn't mention that, I was heading to Fort Bliss.

1165
01:13:29,000 --> 01:13:35,000
And my wife was expecting momentarily.

1166
01:13:35,000 --> 01:13:45,000
They put my orders in delay, permitted me to stay in the Philadelphia area.

1167
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:50,000
Well, she delivered, but at that time, they sent me to Fort Momif, which not too far away.

1168
01:13:50,000 --> 01:13:54,000
I sent to a signal unit there while we waited.

1169
01:13:54,000 --> 01:13:57,000
Our first daughter of born, Shirley.

1170
01:13:57,000 --> 01:14:03,000
And then I went to Fort Bliss.

1171
01:14:03,000 --> 01:14:13,000
And the family never came down there because it was just right and went right for the family to move and stuff like that.

1172
01:14:13,000 --> 01:14:18,000
The second daughter of born when we're hanging off to Korea.

1173
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:25,000
She had born on July.

1174
01:14:25,000 --> 01:14:28,000
We took off from the Fort Lewis in July.

1175
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:34,000
She had born September.

1176
01:14:34,000 --> 01:14:37,000
And still told my parents relations.

1177
01:14:37,000 --> 01:14:41,000
Well, I left the post at Fort Lewis.

1178
01:14:41,000 --> 01:14:47,000
We had to stay at the guest house.

1179
01:14:47,000 --> 01:14:50,000
And I made arrangements for them to stay there.

1180
01:14:50,000 --> 01:15:01,000
And by the time I was heading overseas, my wife had a problem with the manager at the guest house.

1181
01:15:01,000 --> 01:15:06,000
One more thing, which you saw a deal with.

1182
01:15:06,000 --> 01:15:12,000
While the army, military portion was segregated.

1183
01:15:12,000 --> 01:15:15,000
Some of the post facility weren't.

1184
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:21,000
We still have the mentality of our civilians.

1185
01:15:21,000 --> 01:15:30,000
And my mother had flown in from Philadelphia to drive my family back to Philadelphia.

1186
01:15:30,000 --> 01:15:33,000
My mother was a very interesting person.

1187
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:37,000
She'd go any place, fly, drive, whatever.

1188
01:15:37,000 --> 01:15:42,000
And so she drove the car with my wife, her first child.

1189
01:15:42,000 --> 01:15:46,000
My company commander and his wife, who was also pregnant,

1190
01:15:46,000 --> 01:15:49,000
which may have speak to why my company commander picked me to meet him.

1191
01:15:49,000 --> 01:15:51,000
He could trust me.

1192
01:15:51,000 --> 01:15:53,000
And our dog.

1193
01:15:53,000 --> 01:15:59,000
And they drove back from Fort Lewis to Philadelphia.

1194
01:15:59,000 --> 01:16:05,000
Had no problems in route.

1195
01:16:05,000 --> 01:16:08,000
They got tremendous treatment.

1196
01:16:08,000 --> 01:16:14,000
Went to Columbus, Ohio, where my company commander, wife, was going.

1197
01:16:14,000 --> 01:16:17,000
And their child didn't continue to want to fill it.

1198
01:16:17,000 --> 01:16:20,000
Excuse me, fill it off you.

1199
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:25,000
My mother got her first treatment speedin' ticket on Pennsylvania Turnbike.

1200
01:16:25,000 --> 01:16:29,000
They explained it to who they were.

1201
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:36,000
The center of the trooper was very polite and said, OK, go on, but take it easy.

1202
01:16:36,000 --> 01:16:39,000
But my mother wanted, she'd like to drive.

1203
01:16:39,000 --> 01:16:41,000
Heavy foot.

1204
01:16:41,000 --> 01:16:47,000
And I got to the point that I had to since I was one in charge now.

1205
01:16:47,000 --> 01:16:49,000
And she was living in our house.

1206
01:16:49,000 --> 01:16:53,000
The next bean ticket you get, that's going to be it.

1207
01:16:53,000 --> 01:16:56,000
Because I control the insurance and we can't go through it.

1208
01:16:56,000 --> 01:16:58,000
You kill yourself.

1209
01:16:58,000 --> 01:17:03,000
But she, OK.

1210
01:17:03,000 --> 01:17:10,000
Now I'm hanging off to, I just had to put that in because she was part of the program.

1211
01:17:10,000 --> 01:17:12,000
I go off to Germany.

1212
01:17:12,000 --> 01:17:17,000
That was probably more scared during that conversation than during some of your combat periods.

1213
01:17:17,000 --> 01:17:19,000
Yes.

1214
01:17:19,000 --> 01:17:34,000
We're going off to Germany and join the second Army division in West Germany.

1215
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:40,000
Mike Johnson-Hime is our location where my unit was located.

1216
01:17:40,000 --> 01:17:44,000
And I was in combat command B, CCB.

1217
01:17:44,000 --> 01:17:49,000
I'm now a captain, communication train.

1218
01:17:49,000 --> 01:17:55,000
And I became the communication officer for the battalion.

1219
01:17:55,000 --> 01:17:59,000
42nd Army and infantry battalion.

1220
01:17:59,000 --> 01:18:05,000
And my did a pretty good job.

1221
01:18:05,000 --> 01:18:08,000
Learn how to do things with the communication.

1222
01:18:08,000 --> 01:18:12,000
I became a Mars military amateur radio.

1223
01:18:12,000 --> 01:18:20,000
And I set up the Mars station for the regiment.

1224
01:18:20,000 --> 01:18:25,000
And we named it the station after CCB, the regiment.

1225
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:29,000
And the commander of it, I'll be happier because his regiment had a Mars station.

1226
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:31,000
No one else had one.

1227
01:18:31,000 --> 01:18:33,000
And so I became a tall cut.

1228
01:18:33,000 --> 01:18:37,000
And I got to think that not many of people could have gotten.

1229
01:18:37,000 --> 01:18:47,000
And continued training at this time in my Germany.

1230
01:18:47,000 --> 01:18:58,000
I now have been over there long enough to come home and doing this training after having my communications training.

1231
01:18:58,000 --> 01:19:04,000
I became a company commander, which made it my third company.

1232
01:19:04,000 --> 01:19:10,000
And company in combat, even though it was terminated short time, but still did the work.

1233
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:14,000
Company at any time, depth, training company.

1234
01:19:14,000 --> 01:19:19,000
And I got another infantry company, armored infantry, and we trained pretty hard.

1235
01:19:19,000 --> 01:19:22,000
I had personal carriers as a movement.

1236
01:19:22,000 --> 01:19:25,000
Armored plates still for it.

1237
01:19:25,000 --> 01:19:32,000
I returned to the States.

1238
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:41,000
It is now 57.

1239
01:19:41,000 --> 01:19:53,000
I'd gone to, by the way, back to Fort Benning for Advanced course training before going to Germany.

1240
01:19:53,000 --> 01:20:03,000
And I feel to mention that we had our third child there at Fort Benning.

1241
01:20:03,000 --> 01:20:08,000
Now, are you seeing racial change in the Army?

1242
01:20:08,000 --> 01:20:09,000
The Army is for it.

1243
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:12,000
Yes, it's going through many changes.

1244
01:20:12,000 --> 01:20:20,000
And by this time, at Benning, that time, I was completely integrated, integrated unit.

1245
01:20:20,000 --> 01:20:30,000
And by the time I got to Germany, totally integrated, integrated, but yet absolutely certain people.

1246
01:20:30,000 --> 01:20:49,000
So the signal officer, this senior black officer in the division, was a black lieutenant colonel assigned to our army.

1247
01:20:49,000 --> 01:20:56,000
Assigned to our technical service trains, as we call them.

1248
01:20:56,000 --> 01:21:03,000
And when it got time for a battalion commander to change, we were encouraging him to become a new battalion commander.

1249
01:21:03,000 --> 01:21:10,000
I knew enough people at the division because I had, as a signal officer, I used to, as a communicator, I used to deal with folks at the division.

1250
01:21:10,000 --> 01:21:13,000
And when it was an operation, I dealt with the people there.

1251
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:23,000
And I tried to encourage this Lieutenant Colonel to come down and join it because we had fine battalion, and he was qualified.

1252
01:21:23,000 --> 01:21:32,000
And the interesting part about his name was Johnson, but his wife was, he may have heard of baseball player Campanillo.

1253
01:21:32,000 --> 01:21:37,000
His wife was from that family.

1254
01:21:38,000 --> 01:21:48,000
With that name, he could have gotten anything he wanted to, but he decided, no, he would just stay where he is because he accompanied me at Regis here, but the executive officer of a unit, not a combat unit.

1255
01:21:48,000 --> 01:21:52,000
And so, he stayed up there, so we did our thing.

1256
01:21:52,000 --> 01:21:57,000
It's now time for me to come back to the stage.

1257
01:21:57,000 --> 01:22:03,000
I was on ROTC duty, mind you, I did not have a degree.

1258
01:22:03,000 --> 01:22:09,000
And I was assigned to a place called Prairie View.

1259
01:22:09,000 --> 01:22:28,000
I went, there's a captain, assigned to the military, assigned to the department, the only captain in the unit, a Lieutenant Colonel, three majors, and me, captain.

1260
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:31,000
The junior officer.

1261
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:33,000
A couple of challenges.

1262
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:38,000
When I went to that job, I was sent there by a very good friend who now in the department of Army.

1263
01:22:38,000 --> 01:22:43,000
He said, you go down to Prairie View and get your go to school. Take classes, get your degree.

1264
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:45,000
Roger that?

1265
01:22:45,000 --> 01:22:54,000
So, when I get, we get to Prairie View, and, on by the way, from racial standpoint, while driving down there,

1266
01:22:54,000 --> 01:23:00,000
we were told by some friends from Germany.

1267
01:23:00,000 --> 01:23:07,000
Now, when you go down, you stop by white friends, when you go to Mississippi, stop by this place.

1268
01:23:07,000 --> 01:23:11,000
My parents are there, see them, and they'll take care of you.

1269
01:23:11,000 --> 01:23:13,000
Try me through.

1270
01:23:13,000 --> 01:23:19,000
Now, make sure you don't talk to two people.

1271
01:23:19,000 --> 01:23:26,000
One is the mother, they talk to my father, they don't talk to my mother, and he'll understand.

1272
01:23:26,000 --> 01:23:33,000
Don't talk to her, she won't understand, because I'm still blind, and they still haven't gotten to that point.

1273
01:23:33,000 --> 01:23:42,000
I might add also, going there, that while we're in Germany, I keep forgetting these things now.

1274
01:23:43,000 --> 01:23:47,000
While in Germany, my mother and mother-law joined us.

1275
01:23:47,000 --> 01:24:01,000
They came over to visit with us to see Europe, trip over there, and we convinced my wife's mother to stay with us.

1276
01:24:01,000 --> 01:24:06,000
My father finally got tired. He said, when are you coming home, Rose Bechton?

1277
01:24:06,000 --> 01:24:10,000
And she got the message, so she got home and came back.

1278
01:24:10,000 --> 01:24:14,000
She had a good time, mom had a good time, stay with us.

1279
01:24:14,000 --> 01:24:22,000
And that made a family comfortable, because my mother-law with us took everything, and she stayed with us until she died.

1280
01:24:22,000 --> 01:24:34,000
And I might also add that while she was with us, whenever there was a disagreement in my family, in myself, my mom was on my side, which irritated Louise, no in.

1281
01:24:34,000 --> 01:24:37,000
That's no story.

1282
01:24:37,000 --> 01:24:52,000
Why did at time we get to Texas, per review, with three daughters, the third one was born while at Fort Benning,

1283
01:24:52,000 --> 01:24:59,000
and she's from her background, per certificate, Reese Georgia.

1284
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:08,000
And it was also in Columbus, Georgia, that my wife learned how to drive and get driver's license,

1285
01:25:08,000 --> 01:25:15,000
and the policeman who checked her out for driving.

1286
01:25:15,000 --> 01:25:25,000
He got into the car, and Louise got on the driver's side, and he said, okay, told her to do certain things.

1287
01:25:25,000 --> 01:25:38,000
And she drove probably less than a block, turned around because the police over the door, parked the car, got out, you passed.

1288
01:25:38,000 --> 01:25:51,000
And I later found out that the officer was so impressed by the way that she controlled herself, the way she got into the car, where she adjusted everything, and how she made the U-turn and parked the car, that's enough for him.

1289
01:25:51,000 --> 01:25:53,000
That was her driver's license.

1290
01:25:53,000 --> 01:26:03,000
Okay, we're now at Fort down at per review.

1291
01:26:03,000 --> 01:26:14,000
We got a house ridden from an old map professor who had a second house.

1292
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:20,000
My professor, Military Science, my boss, was Lieutenant Colonel.

1293
01:26:20,000 --> 01:26:27,000
I said we got three majors and myself, and I had my instructor, my group, what the teaching of juniors.

1294
01:26:27,000 --> 01:26:32,000
Military Science 3 is the specification.

1295
01:26:32,000 --> 01:26:48,000
There are no white students, a few white faculty, and I was the only combat experienced officer in this group.

1296
01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:54,000
I mean, late war, we had something reward too.

1297
01:26:54,000 --> 01:27:03,000
And when I announced to Professor Military Science, I'm going to take courses, and he blew up.

1298
01:27:03,000 --> 01:27:06,000
There's no way in the world you can take a course that worked for me.

1299
01:27:06,000 --> 01:27:15,000
Sir, I was sent down here. You're assigned here, right? Yes, sir. You can't take courses.

1300
01:27:15,000 --> 01:27:22,000
In work as a student, I should also point out that in this building, I was also his assistant.

1301
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:29,000
We went to my office, right outside the office, we're just located.

1302
01:27:29,000 --> 01:27:42,000
The next day, after we had this little blow up, I reported in about 7.30, the Colonel comes in about 30 minutes later.

1303
01:27:42,000 --> 01:27:48,000
I told him this door, which is not, which is usual.

1304
01:27:48,000 --> 01:27:54,000
In a few minutes, I get a call. Back then, get in here. Yes, sir.

1305
01:27:54,000 --> 01:27:59,000
I go in his office, report it. All right. He even took the courses.

1306
01:27:59,000 --> 01:28:07,000
But let me tell you one thing. If there's any indication whatsoever, is interfering with your being an instructor, you're in trouble.

1307
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:18,000
Yes, sir. I understand that. No question about kosher. I came back outside, and my couple of sergeants, they knew what was going on.

1308
01:28:18,000 --> 01:28:29,000
They smiled. Two or three majors were roaming back and forth. They got worried that the doctor could take courses now.

1309
01:28:29,000 --> 01:28:38,000
The third major was the exec that he had his own office. I'm pointing out he's out to present the climate.

1310
01:28:38,000 --> 01:28:52,000
I am now a regular Army captain, the only regular Army officer in the group, the only non-collect graduate, the only one had been combat recently.

1311
01:28:52,000 --> 01:29:00,000
Now, I got my way by going to taking courses. I'm a target for a lot of people to shoot at.

1312
01:29:00,000 --> 01:29:08,000
But I was pretty good at what I did. I did a good instructor, and I did well academically.

1313
01:29:08,000 --> 01:29:20,000
I should point out that I develop a relationship with the students that even to this day, we're still very close to each other.

1314
01:29:20,000 --> 01:29:34,000
I am now a processing graduation, been there for two years. The last year I'm there, the Army pays for my going to school.

1315
01:29:34,000 --> 01:29:42,000
They had a final semester plan. When you get within your final semester graduation, the Army footed the bill for books and everything.

1316
01:29:42,000 --> 01:29:53,000
That took no worries from that standpoint. I was able to do my job being a instructor, able to get what the doing classes quite well.

1317
01:29:53,000 --> 01:30:02,000
I was able to influence the Professor Military Science. A new one came in by that time.

1318
01:30:02,000 --> 01:30:14,000
He understood what I was doing. He was then a colonel who came in to become the Professor Military Science.

1319
01:30:14,000 --> 01:30:22,000
He was able to influence the person coming in to be the commencement speaker who I had met back when I was in Washington.

1320
01:30:22,000 --> 01:30:38,000
We're now 1960. Time for a commencement. Receive my degree. The commencement speaker makes some reference to Captain Bechton.

1321
01:30:38,000 --> 01:30:44,000
It's such a good man, great reputation. This did not hurt him with reputation in the schools.

1322
01:30:44,000 --> 01:31:02,000
My fellow students smile and the professors smile and stuff like that. When I crossed the stage to get my diploma degree, the person reading off the graduate, listed graduate, stopped the movement.

1323
01:31:02,000 --> 01:31:15,000
Wait a minute. Captain Bechton is a 5,000 graduate of Per View A&M University. Now the chance of my being a 5,000 graduate like a snowball in the hill. I don't believe it.

1324
01:31:15,000 --> 01:31:24,000
But the 5,000 graduate played during that period and it's convenient for the Army and for the university to use that opportunity.

1325
01:31:24,000 --> 01:31:31,000
I walked off the 5,000 graduate that smiling and got my degree, we're in Torcontan.

1326
01:31:31,000 --> 01:31:43,000
Okay. I now have a diploma, went back into the Army,

1327
01:31:43,000 --> 01:31:54,000
went off to the Command General Staff College.

1328
01:31:54,000 --> 01:32:08,000
They school for particularly selected young captains and majors, and Lieutenant Crownfoot, particularly young captains.

1329
01:32:08,000 --> 01:32:17,000
I'm now a regular Army officer in the school at Command General Staff College at Fort Leb Worry.

1330
01:32:17,000 --> 01:32:29,000
And peers support. Could not ask for more because I met people in Germany at any town gap in elsewhere.

1331
01:32:29,000 --> 01:32:44,000
My student company commander at the Fort Benning who was a Lieutenant Colonel, he maintained relationships with me.

1332
01:32:44,000 --> 01:32:50,000
He later became a division commander, which is rather important.

1333
01:32:50,000 --> 01:33:03,000
I'm now at Fort Leb Worry, tough academic work, working very hard to get through.

1334
01:33:03,000 --> 01:33:10,000
While there I become a major.

1335
01:33:10,000 --> 01:33:27,000
The Army is still not that overrun by black officer, but in my class at Leb Worry, we had 16 black officers out of 600.

1336
01:33:27,000 --> 01:33:36,000
And we sort of kept together as a group, except for one. He was Lieutenant Colonel.

1337
01:33:36,000 --> 01:33:43,000
He felt that he was above him, dignity, dignity, to associate with major's junior to him.

1338
01:33:43,000 --> 01:33:51,000
So to make a long story short, we got through, he failed academically. The rest of us made it.

1339
01:33:51,000 --> 01:33:58,000
We studied for exams, and he reviewed the joint for studying. And we went through. We worked together.

1340
01:33:58,000 --> 01:34:15,000
We're together. From Leb Worry, it is now in the 62, graduate in 61.

1341
01:34:15,000 --> 01:34:26,000
Kennedy has become the president. Had to little freak us down in Mexico, Cuban, whatever you want to call it.

1342
01:34:26,000 --> 01:34:43,000
And they started their little mess around in Germany. And before we left Leb Worry, we had orders to France.

1343
01:34:43,000 --> 01:34:59,000
Of that group that went to France, six of us went to the communications zone in France out of class, which is, for come out of our officers, not all that good, we thought.

1344
01:34:59,000 --> 01:35:09,000
And we started, why us? Why aren't we going to Germany to become, you know, where the real Army is, not technicians, logisticians, stuff like that?

1345
01:35:09,000 --> 01:35:22,000
I found I got the message someone else got it, that the commander in the communications zone, France had complained about not getting his fair share of talent.

1346
01:35:22,000 --> 01:35:35,000
And of the six of us going into France, two of us were black, one was just Lieutenant Colonel who failed at Leb Worry.

1347
01:35:35,000 --> 01:35:43,000
And I ended up in the same unit that he was, which a very interesting story, no, the story. He finally decided to talk.

1348
01:35:43,000 --> 01:35:55,000
And I got a pretty good job. He went to logistic G4. And I was in operations, G3 became eventually a chief of plants and operations.

1349
01:35:55,000 --> 01:36:11,000
In France, my job was to prepare for the evacuation of US forces, families from Germany after passing through with me at the Russians across the border, or each German across the border.

1350
01:36:11,000 --> 01:36:22,000
We get them out back to the stage. And I got pretty good at doing that too, I might add.

1351
01:36:22,000 --> 01:36:32,000
In the meantime, this Lieutenant Colonel who failed Leb Worry, he sort of gotten more troubles in his job. But I just ignore him.

1352
01:36:32,000 --> 01:36:47,000
His wife was livid because we were doing so well, family doing so well with, and we had our foreg, and we had a foreg, and we had a foreg, now at Leb, at Prairie View, our fourth daughter was born.

1353
01:36:47,000 --> 01:37:00,000
And I might ask, I keep forgetting to say, my wife doing that period, she worked to get her degree and became a staff nurse in the college nursing.

1354
01:37:00,000 --> 01:37:14,000
And we did such a great job so that when the dean left, my wife was asked to be the acting dean for the period where the dean was not getting her doctoral study complete.

1355
01:37:14,000 --> 01:37:25,000
So you got this young R N B S who had did so well that the president of college said, okay, you be the acting dean.

1356
01:37:25,000 --> 01:37:32,000
That did not make the other nurses very comfortable who bid her for some time, but they respected her.

1357
01:37:32,000 --> 01:37:52,000
And I'm making a point of this because that's so my fourth daughter was born. I took time to do that. And she had developed a relationship with the doctor so that he suggested she go to Himstead, which is nearby town rather than having the birth at the university.

1358
01:37:52,000 --> 01:38:00,000
So she delivered there. They very first mailed us, see her, what the professor military scientist, knew Colonel, he came in.

1359
01:38:00,000 --> 01:38:15,000
And as I said, he was a great guy. He was the air force. When I was on the campus working in also in class, he later became her godfather.

1360
01:38:15,000 --> 01:38:26,000
I might add that this daughter went on to become a Colonel Air Force. And she's now Colonel Air Force retired. So time that goes on.

1361
01:38:26,000 --> 01:38:27,000
Okay.

1362
01:38:27,000 --> 01:38:30,000
Let me ask you one question or a couple of questions.

1363
01:38:30,000 --> 01:38:31,000
Sure.

1364
01:38:31,000 --> 01:38:41,000
During this period, were you keeping track of, I mean, you're in a military world in some ways, but there's the wider world as well.

1365
01:38:41,000 --> 01:38:49,000
There's a lot of change going on. So there are in, especially in terms of race issues and with the Montgomery bus.

1366
01:38:49,000 --> 01:38:57,000
All those change came up and we were a C. Keelya were of it. And many of I and my peers.

1367
01:38:57,000 --> 01:39:02,000
Like we decide we just like we're demonstrating how good we can be doing our job in the Army.

1368
01:39:02,000 --> 01:39:06,000
We don't have to get out there and parade with placard or join any setting and stuff like that.

1369
01:39:06,000 --> 01:39:12,000
So we think we're doing a better job helping race relations by proving that we can make it.

1370
01:39:12,000 --> 01:39:21,000
And that's was our relationship with the public and with peers who are no longer in the military. And they understood.

1371
01:39:21,000 --> 01:39:28,000
And when I later became a president of a unit president of Pervy A&M University.

1372
01:39:28,000 --> 01:39:32,000
And that's, of course, in K-MOT. What were you doing during the war?

1373
01:39:32,000 --> 01:39:40,000
Fighting protecting you. That's what I'm doing. And they understood that too. And it helped.

1374
01:39:40,000 --> 01:39:46,000
We saw we have friends who. Not military who were involved.

1375
01:39:46,000 --> 01:39:54,000
For turning. He's gotten involved. My wife was sorority and academic sorority I might add.

1376
01:39:54,000 --> 01:39:58,000
Her group did things for the.

1377
01:39:58,000 --> 01:40:06,000
Seterans and for other people. But did they get involved in those kind of thing? No.

1378
01:40:06,000 --> 01:40:11,000
Where it came home to haunt us, I might add.

1379
01:40:11,000 --> 01:40:16,000
Was when my daughter Karen.

1380
01:40:16,000 --> 01:40:22,000
Who went to second daughter born and she went off to South Dakota.

1381
01:40:22,000 --> 01:40:25,000
Don't ask me how she got to South Dakota but I still don't know.

1382
01:40:25,000 --> 01:40:32,000
She heard that good schools and a couple of her friends suggested she go there. So she went there.

1383
01:40:32,000 --> 01:40:36,000
And.

1384
01:40:36,000 --> 01:40:45,000
This took place when I was in Korea. And when.

1385
01:40:45,000 --> 01:40:50,000
I heard that she was gotten free.

1386
01:40:50,000 --> 01:40:58,000
Good student. Her participation was writing letters for the local newspapers.

1387
01:40:58,000 --> 01:41:02,000
Campus newspapers. Anti-war.

1388
01:41:02,000 --> 01:41:07,000
Articles. And when I heard that, of course, you knew I blew up.

1389
01:41:07,000 --> 01:41:14,000
Remind her where she's from, what she did. I never once see an article written by you about anti-military.

1390
01:41:14,000 --> 01:41:19,000
She stopped writing. Naturally she stopped writing but we were paying the bill for her going to school.

1391
01:41:19,000 --> 01:41:25,000
That was one thing.

1392
01:41:25,000 --> 01:41:30,000
We had there are marches.

1393
01:41:30,000 --> 01:41:34,000
We did not participate. We understood what they're doing.

1394
01:41:34,000 --> 01:41:38,000
And we maintained by doing our job in military to the best of our ability.

1395
01:41:38,000 --> 01:41:42,000
Help the overall. Opportunity what they're trying to do.

1396
01:41:42,000 --> 01:41:45,000
I still believe that today.

1397
01:41:45,000 --> 01:41:51,000
Was there some pride in the fact that the military had pioneered in integration.

1398
01:41:51,000 --> 01:41:54,000
Even though it was bumpy, of course, but they did.

1399
01:41:54,000 --> 01:41:59,000
It was realized by a lot of people, certainly not in the military, what did the public do?

1400
01:41:59,000 --> 01:42:08,000
That the integration in the military, it would black majors, black students,

1401
01:42:08,000 --> 01:42:14,000
academicians were doing on a college campus.

1402
01:42:14,000 --> 01:42:23,000
And in the military itself, we're making things happen, good things happen because.

1403
01:42:23,000 --> 01:42:30,000
With a Tuskegee Airman, proving that they could do that, what they're doing.

1404
01:42:30,000 --> 01:42:35,000
We had senior officers were able to get things done.

1405
01:42:35,000 --> 01:42:41,000
And it wasn't too long thereafter because I became a major general.

1406
01:42:41,000 --> 01:42:45,000
I mean, a Brigadier General, Colonel First and Brigadier General.

1407
01:42:45,000 --> 01:42:49,000
And I had command and.

1408
01:42:49,000 --> 01:42:54,000
Our first command was at Fort Hood as a brigade commander.

1409
01:42:54,000 --> 01:43:02,000
Colonel in the same unit that was a communication officer for back in Germany.

1410
01:43:02,000 --> 01:43:07,000
Excuse me.

1411
01:43:07,000 --> 01:43:13,000
The same relationship I made in Germany I was still continued.

1412
01:43:13,000 --> 01:43:23,000
And again, how in the military back at Levent worth and for our left Levent worth in France.

1413
01:43:23,000 --> 01:43:25,000
In the military, we float around.

1414
01:43:25,000 --> 01:43:27,000
We eat each other and things.

1415
01:43:27,000 --> 01:43:29,000
We get to know each other.

1416
01:43:29,000 --> 01:43:41,000
And I said, in France, I was able to help to develop a relationship.

1417
01:43:41,000 --> 01:43:45,000
I did my job very well.

1418
01:43:45,000 --> 01:43:58,000
The Lieutenant Colonel then Colonel of the unit I was in in France became a Colonel.

1419
01:43:58,000 --> 01:44:01,000
And later Brigadier General.

1420
01:44:01,000 --> 01:44:04,000
And we still maintain relationship even though I was there.

1421
01:44:04,000 --> 01:44:08,000
But that time a major Lieutenant Colonel, he just a good guy.

1422
01:44:08,000 --> 01:44:12,000
He was able to help me to get some things done later.

1423
01:44:12,000 --> 01:44:17,000
He spoke up for me on certain occasions.

1424
01:44:17,000 --> 01:44:21,000
And it helped.

1425
01:44:21,000 --> 01:44:25,000
And my peers, black peers, were able to get the same thing.

1426
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:27,000
We knew what we had to do.

1427
01:44:27,000 --> 01:44:29,000
We had our job prepared for it.

1428
01:44:29,000 --> 01:44:31,000
And we advanced in the ranks.

1429
01:44:31,000 --> 01:44:33,000
And we're respected for what we did.

1430
01:44:33,000 --> 01:44:36,000
We got to certain schools because of what we've done.

1431
01:44:36,000 --> 01:44:39,000
Not because we're black but because we're good at what we did.

1432
01:44:39,000 --> 01:44:47,000
And to this day, I have a relationship with people.

1433
01:44:47,000 --> 01:44:51,000
That call I just had, I'm going to return.

1434
01:44:51,000 --> 01:44:55,000
This is a Colonel who was tired from the Army.

1435
01:44:55,000 --> 01:44:59,000
He is now a civilian in the Department of Army.

1436
01:44:59,000 --> 01:45:02,000
They call them SCSRs these days.

1437
01:45:02,000 --> 01:45:07,000
A senior person working in personnel.

1438
01:45:07,000 --> 01:45:09,000
He's going to tell me something.

1439
01:45:09,000 --> 01:45:11,000
What's taking place in the Army today.

1440
01:45:11,000 --> 01:45:15,000
He understands what I've been doing, what I have done.

1441
01:45:15,000 --> 01:45:19,000
And going ahead a little bit, I have been asked to do certain things.

1442
01:45:19,000 --> 01:45:22,000
What a Congress.

1443
01:45:22,000 --> 01:45:27,000
Several years ago, the Congress set up a commission for diversity in the military,

1444
01:45:27,000 --> 01:45:30,000
military leadership diversity.

